length of last word

LengthOfLastWord(string s)
1. Trim the string to remove trailing spaces
2. Split the string by spaces
3. Return the length of the last word




reverse string

ReverseString(char[] s)
1. Initialize two pointers: left = 0, right = length of s - 1
2. While left < right:
   a. Swap s[left] and s[right]
   b. Increment left and decrement right




reverse vowels of string

ReverseVowels(string s)
1. Initialize two pointers: left and right
2. While left < right:
   a. If s[left] is a vowel and s[right] is a vowel:
      i. Swap s[left] and s[right]
      ii. Move both pointers inward
   b. If s[left] is not a vowel, increment left
   c. If s[right] is not a vowel, decrement right



number of segments in string

CountSegments(string s)
1. Trim the string
2. Split the string by spaces
3. Count and return the number of non-empty segments




